snippet: Eight Sunni Muslim militiamen were snatched from their houses and killed, while two suicide bombers targeted a Shiite mosque and a cafe.
abstract: Three attacks north of Baghdad, Iraq, kill at least 25 people, latest in a growing series of insurgent strikes.
lead_paragraph: Eight Sunni Muslim militiamen were snatched from their houses and killed, while two suicide bombers targeted a Shiite mosque and a cafe.
